## Advanced: Tagged Templates

You can prefix a template literal with a function name – that function receives the literal parts and interpolated values. This is used in libraries like `styled-components`.

```javascript
function tag(strings, ...values) {
  console.log(strings); // array of text parts
  console.log(values);  // array of interpolated values
}

const name = 'Alice';
tag`Hello ${name}!`;
```

Don't worry about this for now, but know it exists!
